*NOTE:* I haven't tested this on any OS other than Windows 8 but it should
work with Windows 7.

*DISCLAIMER: IF ANYTHING BAD HAPPENS TO YOUR COMPUTER BECAUSE YOU FOLLOW MY
DIRECTIONS, IT IS NOT MY FAULT.*

If you like OS X but have Windows for some reason this post can help. I have
assembled some different tools to make your PC more Mac-ish. Sure, it's not
perfect but it looks pretty close from the outside.

Here is an overview of the free tools that we will use to Mac-ify your PC. I
will give you the instructions step by step later on.

- ObjectDock (For the Mac Dock)
- ObjectBar (For a Finder-like top bar)
- Office Mac Icons (To make Office look cool)
- Mac OS X Lion ObjectDock Theme (includes the stack docklet)
- iCon Dock Icon Pack
- PNG To Icon Converter (the iCon Dock Icon Pack gives you .gif files
  which can't be used by the system. Gif files can be used by
  ObjectDock)
- 7-Zip
- RAR File Open Knife
- Leopard Enhanced ObjectBar Theme

#html.elem("ol")[#html.elem("li")[\#\#\# Get the Tools]]

The first thing that we have to do is get the tools to make your PC look
like a Mac. Here are the individual instructions for each one
of the tools that we will be using.

#html.elem("ul")[#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# ObjectDock]]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://www.stardock.com/products/objectdock/purchase.asp")[http://www.stardock.com/products/objectdock/purchase.asp].
+ Scroll down to the bottom of the page and click on "Download" under
  "FREE!" (you don't get all of the features but you get enough to
  have a Dock-like experience.
+ Enter in your email address and click submit.
+ Once you get the link to the download, click on it to the the site
  download, click "Download Now".
+ Once it's downloaded, click on the .exe file to start the setup.
+ Click "I agree to the terms of this license agreement" and click
  "Next".
+ Uncheck everything on the next page. Click "Next".
+ If you want to install to a different location, selected it and
  click "Next".

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# ObjectBar]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://download.cnet.com/ObjectBar/3000-2072_4-10069555.html")[http://download.cnet.com/ObjectBar/3000-2072\_4-10069555.html].
+ Click "Download Now".
+ Open the .exe file
+ Click "I Agree".
+ Click "Next" twice.
+ Change the destination folder if you want and then click "Next"
  twice.

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# OfficeMac Icons]

+ NOTE: YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS STEP IF YOU DON'T HAVE OFFICE \
  Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://nkear5.deviantart.com/art/Office-2011-ICNS-PNG-and-ICO-166159609")[http://nkear5.deviantart.com/art/Office-2011-ICNS-PNG-and-ICO-166159609].
+ Click "Download File". It is in the right column under the "More
  like this" section.
+ Remember where you saved the ZIP file.

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# Mac OS X Lion ObjectDock Theme]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://mrwhiteeye.deviantart.com/art/Mac-OS-X-Lion-ObjectDock-Theme-200236930")[http://mrwhiteeye.deviantart.com/art/Mac-OS-X-Lion-ObjectDock-Theme-200236930].
+ Click "Download File". It is in the right column under the "More
  like this" section.
+ Remember where you saved the file.

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# iCon Dock Icon Pack]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://magnumhearted.deviantart.com/art/Mac-Dock-Icons-The-iCon-151583728")[http://magnumhearted.deviantart.com/art/Mac-Dock-Icons-The-iCon-151583728].
+ Click "Download File". It is in the right column under the "More
  like this" section.
+ Remember where you saved the file.

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# PNG to Icon Converter]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://download.cnet.com/PNG-To-Icon-Converter/3000-2195_4-75454150.html")[http://download.cnet.com/PNG-To-Icon-Converter/3000-2195\_4-75454150.html].
+ Click "Download Now".
+ Run the executable that you just downloaded.
+ *WARNING: FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY OR YOU WILL END UP WITH
  A LOT OF JUNK ON YOUR COMPUTER* \
  Click "Next Step"
+ Click *"Decline"* do #emph[not]click accept because that will accept
  the terms and install whatever the terms of service is for (it isn't
  the terms of service for the PNG to Icon Converter).
+ Repeat step 5 until you get to Step 4 of 6. Here you want to uncheck
  the check boxes in the text. Then click "Next Step".
+ The software will download. Once it's done, click "Install Now".
+ The second installer (the one that actually installs the program)
  will come up. Click "Next".
+ Change the destination folder if you want, then click "Next".
+ Change the Start Menu folder if you want, then click "Next".
+ Click "Install".
+ Uncheck "Launch PNG To Icon Converter Now" and then click "Finish".

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# 7-Zip]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://www.7-zip.org/")[http://www.7-zip.org].
+ Click on the appropriate download link (there are two, one of 32-bit
  and one for 64-bit).
+ Once the file has downloaded, run the .exe/.msi file.
+ Click "Next".
+ Check "I accept the terms in the License Agreement" and click
  "Next".
+ Click "Next" (unless you want to change what's installed)
+ Click "Install".
+ Click "Finish".

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# RAR File Open Knife]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://download.cnet.com/RAR-File-Open-Knife-Free-Opener/3000-2250_4-10971016.html")[http://download.cnet.com/RAR-File-Open-Knife-Free-Opener/3000-2250\_4-10971016.html].
+ Click "Download Now".
+ Once it's downloaded, run the .exe file.
+ *WARNING: FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS CAREFULLY OR YOU WILL END UP WITH
  A LOT OF JUNK ON YOUR COMPUTER* \
  Click "Next Step"
+ Check "Custom Installation" and uncheck "Install Coupon Companion".
+ Click "Next".
+ Click "Install Now"
+ Click "OK" unless you want to change the install language.
+ Click "Next" then "I Agree".
+ Uncheck the "I want to install Dragons of Atlantis and the Findr
  Toolbar for free" box and click "Next".
+ Change the install location if you want and click "Install".
+ Uncheck "Run RAR File Open Knife - Free Opener 3.40" and click
  "Finish".

#html.elem("li")[\#\#\#\# Leopard Enhanced ObjectBar Theme]

+ Navigate in your browser to
  #link("http://www.markraats.com/Object%20Bar%20Themes.htm")[http://www.markraats.com/Object%20Bar%20Themes.htm].
+ Click on Part 1 and Part 2
+ Remember where you saved the ZIP folders
+ === Make it Happen <posts-technology-how-to-mac-ify-your-pc-make-it-happen>

  - ==== Set up the Dock <posts-technology-how-to-mac-ify-your-pc-set-up-the-dock>

    + To begin, open to the Mac OS X Lion ObjectDock Theme ZIP
      folder.
    + Copy Mac OS X Lion Dock to C:\\Program
      Files\\Stardock\\ObjectDockFree\\Backgrounds (For 32-bit) \
      OR C:\\Program Files
      (x86)\\Stardock\\ObjectDockFree\\Backgrounds (For 64-bit) \
      _NOTE: IF YOU THOUGHT THAT OBJECTDOCK WAS REALLY COOL AND
      WENT AHEAD AND BOUGHT IT, YOU WILL HAVE TO REPLACE
      "ObjectDockFree" WITH "ObjecDock" IN THIS STEP AND THE NEXT
      STEP._
    + Now copy the StarDocklet folder in the ZIP folder that you
      downloaded to C:\\Program
      Files\\Stardock\\ObjectDockFree\\Docklets (For 32-bit) \
      OR C:\\Program Files
      (x86)\\Stardock\\ObjectDockFree\\Docklets (For 64-bit)
    + Set up an Office DockletNow. To do this, we need to put
      shortcuts to the programs in a new folder so that the Stack
      Docklet can display them. If you have Office (any kind) do
      the following steps:

      + Make a new folder somewhere in your user folder. (I used
        C:\\Users\\Sumner\\Dock\\Office for this.)
      + Open the folder containing the Office executables in it
        (Google it if you don't know where this folder is. I am
        not going to give you an exact folder location because I
        think it is different for the various versions of
        Office. FYI I have Office 2010 and the folder I found
        them in was C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft
        Office\\Office 14.)
      +
    +
